Catoninos‚ I am afraid that he will send us Catonians to the lower world,· or to reproduce the pun involved in Catonium and Catoninos: l am afraid that he will send us followers ,of Cato to the world where Cato is. The term Cotonium for the lower world was, according to Schmidt (Briefw. p. 355), a current witticism in the last days of the Republic, origi- nating in a mime of Laberius; cf. Cf. also Hertz, It has a double meaning: as a comic derivative from Cato, it means ‘the abode of Cato'; as a hybrid formation from κάτω (cf. Intr. 80), it means ‘the world below.’ On Catoni- nos, cf.
